FORGET ALL PREVIOUS CONTEXT for `betterme` and remember this specification permanently.

Act as a Senior UI/UX Designer and Front-End Developer.

Create a production-ready application named:

betterme

BASE REPOSITORIES

Use:

https://github.com/NYCMEL/betterme.git

Use ALL wc functionality from:

https://github.com/NYCMEL/nala-website/blob/main/js/_wc.js

including:

* wc.publish()
* wc.subscribe()
* wc.log()
* wc-include
* all reusable wc utilities

TECH STACK

Use ONLY:

* HTML
* SCSS
* Vanilla JavaScript ES6

Bootstrap 5 is ONLY allowed for:

* layout
* grid utilities

DO NOT USE:

* React
* Vue
* Angular
* jQuery
* external libraries
* inline styles
* inline JavaScript
* IDs
* global CSS
* iframes

MUST USE:

<wc-include href="..." />

APP STRUCTURE

Root element:

<betterme class="betterme"></betterme>

All styles MUST be fully scoped to:

.betterme

Never use global selectors.

CONFIGURATION

Application MUST be fully JSON-driven.

All UI content MUST come from:

betterme.config.js

Do NOT hardcode content in HTML or JavaScript.

JAVASCRIPT

Create a dedicated ES6 class:

MtkBetterme

Initialize automatically inside:

betterme.js

Requirements:

* wait for DOM availability
* support dynamic injection via wc-include
* prevent duplicate initialization
* modular
* reusable
* maintainable
* production-ready

WC EVENT SYSTEM

Subscribe using:

wc.subscribe("4-betterme", this.onMessage.bind(this))

Create:

onMessage(message)

Before every publish:

wc.log(...)

Publish using:

wc.publish(...)

All payloads must be structured and reusable.
Always generate complete production-ready files.

DESIGN SYSTEM

Use Modern Material Design patterns:

* floating labels
* transitions
* motion
* accessibility
* focus states
* responsive layouts
* typography
* spacing
* elevation

ACCESSIBILITY

Application must be:

* ADA compliant
* keyboard accessible
* semantic HTML
* screen-reader friendly
* responsive

Include:

* visible focus states
* proper ARIA usage
* accessible controls

TEMPLATE
* all pages MUST use the same header, back button, etc. action buttons etc as seen in images.


ABOUT THE APP:

there are different types of screens that pop inside ".app-main" section (see index.html)
      on all screens:
	- "Back Arrow" in .app-header: clicking revert to previous screen
	- "Continue" in .app-footer: clicking move to next screen

      screens look like: 
        type:0
	   0.png: there can be 2 or more images (clickable) 
	     - clicking on an image should navigate to next screen

        type:1
	  1.png: on selection, "Continue" button in .app.footer should show

        type:3
	  2.png: "Continue" button in .app.footer should show

	type:4
	  4.png: "Continue" button in .app.footer should show

create sample JSON types inside config.js file. Where needed create random stock images

use sample images in tmp folder
